title: Homotopy Extension Property
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Given a {{topsp}} $$X$$ and a [[Subpsace]] $$A \subseteq X$$, we say $$(X, A)$$ has the ''homotopy extension property'' if:

* for any map $$f : X \to Y$$
* and any [[Homotopy]] $$F : A \times I \to Y$$ with $$F|A \times \{0\} = f|A$$,
* there exists a homotopy $$\hat F : X \times I \to Y$$, such that:
** $$\hat F|X \times \{0\} = f$$
** $$\hat F|A \times I = F$$